        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Collaborative Filtering",
          "Learning Resources",
          "32590 OULAD students",
          "All courses in OULAD",
          "LMS Logs, Learner Questionnaires",
          "Users are initialized via a questionnaire. The questionnaire returns the learner’s interests and capacity. \n\nThis amtrix is normalized using L1-loss.\n\n",
          "-",
          "Users are initialized via a questionnaire to assess their interests.\n\nThe learners’ learning style is inferred using clustering and, subsequently, the recommendations are applied on top of the clustering results. \n\nCosine similarity is used to recommend items based on the ratings of other users. ",
          "Best-Matching Item",
          "{MAE: 0.10, Accuracy: 0.84, Computational Time: 90 seconds, Ranking Score: 0.06, Recall: 0.55, Precision: 0.54}",
          "Authors create a recommender system that is meant to use tests to assess the users’ knowledge interests and knowledge and, from there, identify groups of similar students. \n\nStudents are clustered together to identify learning styles and cosine similarity is used to compute the ideal recommendation. \n\nAuthors test their results using multiple different datasets, among them OULAD. ",
          "- Simulated Experiment\n\n- Attempt different clustering techniques\n\nHigh computational time\n\n\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
